<h1>Claude Strillo</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.claude.works/blog/now">claude.works/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Santa Ana
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
I am a solo artist as 'Claude' and also the founder of Anything Box and The Diary.  I am a painter, writer, and photographer / filmmaker (although I break all the rules).
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help people learn its ok to be themselves through being completely creative
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I feel art has trans-formative powers, enabling the minds and hearts of people to unite.  I write, paint, create music as a way of exploring this force of change, hoping to be the cause of more positivism in the world.  I was given the gift of creating things to help myself, but more so to help others see the wonder that is being alive!
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
That time is the most precious, most expensive, and most highly sought after thing in this world. So we should not waste what little time we have.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“The Four Hour Work Week” by Tim Ferriss is a great one, seriously.  But so is “Creative Visualization” by Shakti Gawain
</p>

